label.Description: Pull requests that update a dependency file

label.Name: do-not-merge
label.Description: DEPRECATED. Indicates that a PR should not merge. Label can only be manually applied/removed.

label.Name: do-not-merge/blocked-paths
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because it touches files in blocked paths.

label.Name: do-not-merge/cherry-pick-not-approved
label.Description: Indicates that a PR is not yet approved to merge into a release branch.

label.Name: do-not-merge/hold
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because someone has issued a /hold command.

label.Name: do-not-merge/invalid-commit-message
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because it has an invalid commit message.

label.Name: do-not-merge/invalid-owners-file
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because it has an invalid OWNERS file in it.

label.Name: do-not-merge/release-note-label-needed
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because it's missing one of the release note labels.

label.Name: do-not-merge/work-in-progress
label.Description: Indicates that a PR should not merge because it is a work in progress.

label.Name: good first issue

label.Name: help wanted
label.Description: Denotes an issue that needs help from a contributor. Must meet "help wanted" guidelines.

label.Name: kind/api-change
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to adding, removing, or otherwise changing an API

label.Name: kind/bug
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a bug.

label.Name: kind/cleanup
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to cleaning up code, process, or technical debt.

label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a feature/enhancement marked for deprecation.

label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to design.

label.Name: kind/documentation
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to documentation.

label.Name: kind/failing-test
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a consistently or frequently failing test.

label.Name: kind/feature
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a new feature.

label.Name: kind/flake
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a flaky test.

label.Name: kind/regression
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a regression from a prior release.

label.Name: kind/releasing
label.Description: issues related to releasing

label.Name: kind/support
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as a support question.

label.Name: kind/test-coverage
label.Description: Categorizes issue or PR as related to a gap in or problem with our test coverage.

label.Name: lgtm
label.Description: "Looks good to me", indicates that a PR is ready to be merged.

label.Name: lifecycle/active
label.Description: Indicates that an issue or PR is actively being worked on by a contributor.

label.Name: lifecycle/frozen
label.Description: Indicates that an issue or PR should not be auto-closed due to staleness.

label.Name: lifecycle/rotten
label.Description: Denotes an issue or PR that has aged beyond stale and will be auto-closed.

label.Name: lifecycle/stale
label.Description: Denotes an issue or PR has remained open with no activity and has become stale.

label.Name: needs-kind
label.Description: Indicates a PR lacks a `kind/foo` label and requires one.

label.Name: needs-ok-to-test
label.Description: Indicates a PR that requires an org member to verify it is safe to test.

label.Name: needs-priority
label.Description: Indicates an issue or PR lacks a `priority/foo` label and requires one.

label.Name: needs-rebase
label.Description: Indicates a PR cannot be merged because it has merge conflicts with HEAD.

label.Name: needs-sig
label.Description: Indicates an issue or PR lacks a `sig/foo` label and requires one.

label.Name: needs-triage
label.Description: Indicates an issue or PR lacks a `triage/foo` label and requires one.

label.Name: ok-to-test
label.Description: Indicates a non-member PR verified by an org member that is safe to test.

label.Name: priority/awaiting-more-evidence
label.Description: Lowest priority. Possibly useful, but not yet enough support to actually get it done.

label.Name: priority/backlog
label.Description: Higher priority than priority/awaiting-more-evidence.

label.Name: priority/critical-urgent
label.Description: Highest priority. Must be actively worked on as someone's top priority right now.

label.Name: priority/important-longterm
label.Description: Important over the long term, but may not be staffed and/or may need multiple releases to complete.

label.Name: priority/important-soon
label.Description: Must be staffed and worked on either currently, or very soon, ideally in time for the next release.

label.Name: release-note
label.Description: Denotes a PR that will be considered when it comes time to generate release notes.

label.Name: release-note-action-required
label.Description: Denotes a PR that introduces potentially breaking changes that require user action.

label.Name: release-note-none
label.Description: Denotes a PR that doesn't merit a release note.
